fo/env endpoints.\\n\\nTo fully utilize the native metadata, it might be beneficial for tests to exercise runtime hints. I’m curious if Spring Boot Actuator has built-in reachability metadata. There’s probably existing metadata in the repository for org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-actuator. I need to inspect that metadata further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jp77ZoRKDl8jAbfDG5koEzBW|fc_03cf3ef44555b2a6016a430865468c8194bc1c7c78cf89095b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find metadata -path '*spring-boot-actuator*' -type f -maxdepth 8 -print -exec sh -c 'echo ===$1; head -100 \"$1\"' _ {} \\;", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 12981, "output": 556, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31969, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782777944559, "responseId": "resp_03cf3ef44555b2a6016a430859360c819499e40f120c6d5f9a"}}
