struct the driver to fix the issue effectively without setup. The LLM could help adapt the tests too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering actuator and testing**\\n\\nI think adding the starter-actuator could improve testing metrics and normal usage, but it’s also an extra artifact not currently in the test. It incorporates spring-boot-actuator-autoconfigure and Micrometer, which might produce unrelated metadata. The user-code-filter allows only org.springframework.boot.actuate, but changing the classpath includes autoconfigure packages. Actually, the starting package does begin with org.springframework.boot.actuate, so it seems valid. I also need to mention that \\\"No Docker images\\\" are used since I rely on in-memory repositories and endpoints. Lastly, JSON needs to be valid, no markdown!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is concretely required. The resolved spring-boot-actuator:3.0.0 artifact only declares spring-boot:3.0.0 as a dependency, and meaningful actuator coverage is reachable through in-memory/core APIs; the reported javac failures are Spring Boot 3.0 API changes rather than missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment or system properties are required. Generated tests should target Spring Boot 3.0 actuator APIs: avoid removed org.springframework.boot.actuate.trace.http.HttpTrace types, use the 3.0 org.springframework.boot.actuate.web.exchanges APIs if HTTP exchange coverage is needed, and adapt changed constructors such as HealthEndpoint, EnvironmentEndpoint, and Sanitizer.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The actuator jar contains optional integration classes for metrics, data stores, web stacks, and messaging that require additional client libraries or services; tests should avoid those optional integrations unless deliberately adding scoped dependencies.\",\n    \"Spring Boot documentation normally recommends spring-boot-starter-actuator for full application auto-configuration, but adding it would broaden the classpath beyond the target artifact and is not necessary for meaningful direct coverage of spring-boot-actuator.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03cf3ef44555b2a6016a43087215ac81949295fd71351f8257\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3520, "output": 964, "cacheRead": 30208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34692, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782777957610, "responseId": "resp_03cf3ef44555b2a6016a4308664ae0819484d9385cc9e6b642"}, "toolResults": []}
